y CE)",1,"low",[192,193],{"_":60,"type":61,"ref":62},{"_":64,"type":65,"ref":66},[195],[69,70],{"_":154,"role":76,"ref":155},{"_":198,"type":80},"KA0849",{"_":200,"mainLang":201,"languages":202},"Ancient Greek","grc",[200],{"n":86,"url":204,"height":88,"width":89,"desc":205,"surfaceType":91},"ISic002750_tiled.tif","I.Sicily with the permission of the Assessorato Regionale dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana - Dipartimento dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana",[],[208,209,210,99],"Supplementum epigraphicum graecum, 1923-","Bulletin épigraphique, 1888-","Manganaro, 1994, Iscrizioni, epigrafi ed epigrammi in Greco della Sicilia orientale di epoca romana",[212,213,214,109],"F2GG87EQ","77P5MNIR","532NF7SV",[216,217,218,130,17,21,117,118,119,120,118,172,219,201],"isic002750","i.sicily inscription 002750",{"_":10},"ancient greek","Text encoding: Francesca Prado, edition source:",{"file":222,"uri":222,"title":223,"status":224,"editionAuthor":11,"type":226,"objectType":230,"material":231,"condition":232,"layoutDesc":234,"handNote":239,"date":387,"places":391,"geo":394,"country":71,"region":72,"settlement":396,"repository":397,"idno":400,"textLang":402,"facsimile":404,"provenance":60,"letterHeights":407,"publications":408,"zotero":411,"keywords":414,"html":420},"ISic002945","A gymnasiarch crowns a group of youths",{"_":225},"edited",{"_":227,"ana":228,"ref":229},"honorific","#function.honorific","http://www.eagle-network.eu/voc/typeins/lod/69.html",{"_":17,"ana":18,"ref":19},{"_":21,"ana":22,"ref":23},{"ana":233},"#condition.fragment",{"layout":235},{"p":236,"rs":237,"damage":238},"15 neatly carved lines of Greek letters, of which the first four are larger. There appears to be a slight vacat at the top; lines 1-3 are indented by the equivalent of 1-2 characters at most; from line 4 onwards the left indentation increases, with clear vacats after lines 5 and 6, and a fixed left margin (c.7 cm vacat) from line 7 onwards; a vacat is consistently inserted between each name in the list from line 7 onwards.",{"_":30,"ana":31,"ref":32},{"ana":34},{"lettering":240,"dimensions":368},[241,242],"Elegant letters with minimal serifs/terminations visible on longer strokes (e.g. on tau, sigma and epsilon). Alpha has straight bar; beta has smaller upper loop, with the two loops connected without meeting the vertical; epsilon has shorter middle bar; theta is a full-size circle with a detached horizontal stroke at the centre; kappa has full length arms; mu has near vertical first and last strokes, with the middle strokes meeting a small way above the baseline; xsi is formed of vertical with three horizontals, the middle one of shorter length; omicron is full-size; pi has equal length vertical strokes; sigma has horizontal topo and bottom strokes; phi is ovoid, with vertical taller than other letters (14-15mm); omega full size, near circular, but open at the base. Traces of a secondary text include lunate epsilon (see commentary).",{"_":243,"ref":244},"\n                                    Types list:\n                                    \n                                    \n                                    \n                                    \n                                    \n                                    \n                                    \n                                    \n                                    \n                                    \n                                    \n                                    \n                                    \n                                    \n                                    \n                                    \n                                    \n                                    \n                                    \n                                    \n                                    \n                                    \n                                    \n                                    \n                                    \n     